def: To restore carbon to; as, to recarbonize iron in converting itinto steel.
One who fogs; a pettifogger. [Obs.]A beggarly fogger. Terence in English(1614)
A small instrument with four strings, played with a bow; afiddle.

The Latin for, "and from the Son," equivalent to et filio,inserted by the third council of Toledo (a. d. 589) in the clause quiex Patre procedit (who proceedeth from the Father) of the Niceno-Constantinopolitan Creed (a. d. 381), which makes a creed state thatthe Holy Ghost proceeds from the Son as well as from the Father.Hence, the doctrine itself (not admitted by the Eastern Church).
The quality of being becoming, appropriate, or fit; congruity;fitness.The becomingness of human nature. Grew.
To assay, or attempt, improperly or unsuccessfully. [Obs.] W.Browne.
The king parrakeet See under King.
The doctrine and usages of Episcopalians; episcopacy.

A plane surface divided in one direction with linesrepresenting hours and minutes, and in the other with linesrepresenting miles, and having diagonals (usually movable strings)representing the speed and position of various trains.
